    <text id="A7607T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Nadenbousch writes his wife a brief note introducing Miss Hieskell, who will
                    convey information and forward Nadenbousch any letters devoid of war news.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-09-22"><abbr expan="September">Sept</abbr> 22/63</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Wife</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>This note will be handed you by Miss M S Hieskell who is on her way to <abbr
                        expan="Philadelphia">Phil<hi rend="super">
                            <hi rend="underline">a</hi>
                        </hi></abbr> to take up residence. I will be glad that you will have her
                    remain with you during her stay in the <unclear>our</unclear>
                    <unclear>Town</unclear> and give her any assistance she may need to help her on
                    her journey. introduce her to Cousin Mary L. Kelley. she will hand you a note
                    from me &amp; Can give you some verbal information from me</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours ever</salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="John Quincy Adams">J Q A</abbr> Nadenbousch</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Your husband is very well. I have not time to stop and
                        see you. He says if you Can bring your household furniture Come on, but not
                        otherwise I will forward your letter to him at <unclear>my</unclear>
                        <unclear>home</unclear>. Write only <hi rend="underline">one</hi> page and
                        no war news. Address Miss Mary S. Heiskell 719 Walnut Street Philadelphia.
                            <name type="recipient">M<hi rend="super">
                                <hi rend="underline">rs</hi>
                            </hi>
                            <abbr expan="Hester">H</abbr> J Nadenbousch</name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
